We're ending 2024 with a final update that is going to set all of you up for a prosperous 2025! PRs get merged around this time on `Thursday 19th December` :egirl: 

## **tldr; One league per miner, predictions `<0.5` allowed and official base miner!**

## Single league commitment:
- SN41 is like your gf/bf, no commitment issues here! 😉  because miners now **can only commit to a single league** (as opposed to multiple/all).
- Based on data we've seen *no single model* has performed effectively for *all leagues* so having a dedicated miner/model/uid per league is actually better for scoring
- With the update, the first league in your `miner.env` will be taken as **the single league** your miner is committed too *regardless if there are more leagues in the file*
- The grace period for league commitments is set to 24 hrs. Valis will score the predictions for the last league commitment for up to 24 hrs since their last commitment response. 
- **Miner action: Place the league you want to be committed to at the beginning of the `miner.env` list.**

## No minimum win probability:
- Previously we've restricted predictions to being `<0.5`. This is now lifted.
- With the updated gfilter from last update, **it has been tuned to effectively do the same thing.**
- **No miner action needed** except allowing your model to make predictions of all probabilities again

## Base miner:
- Launching a base miner to give newcomers a start on our subnet as well as a benchmark for us to continually optimize the subnet from
- The base miner will simply pull the odds from api and submit them as a win probability 🙂 From there, you should build your own model using historical odds, players, teams and additional data and pipelines.
- **Miner action: Improve your model! If all base miners (and regular miners) are simply submitting wp from odds, the slightest improvement in edge discovery will send you higher on the metagraph**
- As a fyi: We launched a miner on mainnet to test the base miner. It is **UID 132**

## Good to knows:
- Gfilter constants have been further tweaked
- The update will include bt `8.5.1`
- All updates are live on testnet already
